Dr. Jill Biden spoke at the opening ceremony of the PFLAG National Convention in Alexandria, VA. She discussed the importance of acceptance and support for the LGBTQ+ community, emphasizing the impact it can have on their well-being and success. Dr. Biden highlighted the challenges faced by LGBTQ+ youth, including bullying and harassment, and the need for safe and inclusive school environments. She expressed pride in the progress made by the Obama Administration, such as the signing of the Hate Crimes Prevention Act and the repeal of Don't Ask, Don't Tell. However, she acknowledged that there is still work to be done to ensure equality and support for all. Dr. Biden commended the attendees for their advocacy and encouraged them to continue speaking out and sharing their stories to change hearts and minds. She thanked them for their courage and commitment and expressed gratitude on behalf of the President, Vice President, and the White House.